race.comment: Wide open with a few well-educated first starters too. Sticking with HIGH ON THE HILL (1) though, who was in the market on debut as a juvenile and ran on well for a close-up fourth. Given a long break and resumes here in easier. Has upside and looks tough to stop again. KADESH (7) is a three-start maiden who has placed twice, the latest giving a sight when going down narrowly at Kyneton. Close to a win and looks a leading chance. INSPIRING (2) has raced twice to date and tries to lead throughout ag each finishing fourth. Expected to take running down fresh. GLAMOUR MODEL (6) improved second outing to place at Pakenham and has upside.
